In {{ill|880|ja|880年}} ({{ill|Gangyō|ja|元慶}} 4), {{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|応神天皇}}, {{ill|Ichikishima-hime|ja|市寸島比賣命}}, {{ill|Tagitsu-hime|ja|多岐都比賣神}}, and {{ill|Sumiyoshi Sanjin|ja|住吉大神}} were enshrined alongside and the shrine was named "Ōmiya Hachimangu." It was later renamed to its current name.<ref name="gunshi"/><ref name="rekishiteki-219-232">{{Cite web|和書|date= |url=https://www.city.okazaki.lg.jp/1550/1567/452000/p020134_d/fil/10-02-7.pdf |title=第2章07 額田地区の山里のくらしにみる歴史的風致 |format=PDF |website=[https://www.city.okazaki.lg.jp/1550/1567/452000/p020134.html 岡崎市歴史的風致維持向上計画] |publisher=岡崎市 |accessdate=2022-6-3 }}</ref>

