'''Natsuyama Hachimangu''' (夏山八幡宮) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Natsuyama|ja|夏山町|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Okazaki|ja|岡崎市|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県|qq=draft}}. It is renowned for the {{ill|Natsuyama Hachimangu Fire Festival|ja|夏山八幡宮火祭り|qq=draft}}, held in {{ill|October|ja|10月|qq=draft}}.

== Overview ==
The shrine was established in {{ill|531|ja|531st year|qq=draft}} (25th year of {{ill|Emperor Keitai|ja|継体天皇|qq=draft}}) to enshrine {{ill|Amatsuhikone|ja|天津日子根命|1=Amatsuhikone|qq=draft}}.<ref name="gunshi">愛知縣額田郡誌、pp.353</ref>

In {{ill|880|ja|880th year|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Gangyō|ja|元慶|qq=draft}} 4), {{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|応神天皇|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Ichikishima-hime|ja|市寸島比賣命|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Tagitsu-hime|ja|多岐都比賣神|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Sumiyoshi Sanjin|ja|住吉大神|qq=draft}} were enshrined alongside and the shrine was named "Ōmiya Hachimangu." It was later renamed to its current name.<ref name="gunshi"/><ref name="rekishiteki-219-232">{{Cite web|和書|date= |url=https://www.city.okazaki.lg.jp/1550/1567/452000/p020134_d/fil/10-02-7.pdf |title=第2章07 額田地区の山里のくらしにみる歴史的風致 |format=PDF |website=[https://www.city.okazaki.lg.jp/1550/1567/452000/p020134.html 岡崎市歴史的風致維持向上計画] |publisher=岡崎市 |accessdate=2022-6-3 }}</ref>

On {{ill|October 3|ja|10月3日|qq=draft}} of {{ill|1872|ja|1872nd year|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft}} 5), it was designated as a {{ill|Gōsha|ja|郷社|qq=draft}} under the {{ill|Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|ja|近代社格制度|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|1=Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft}}.<ref name="gunshi"/> It is regarded as a shrine dedicated to the ancestor deity of {{ill|Nukata District|ja|額田郡|qq=draft}}.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=https://okazaki-kanko.jp/event/682 | title=夏山八幡宮火まつり |website=岡崎おでかけナビ |publisher=岡崎市観光協会 |date= | accessdate=2022-1-5 }}</ref>

A {{ill|Mune-fuda|ja|棟札|qq=draft}} dated {{ill|August 14|ja|8月14日|qq=draft}}, 880 (Gangyō 4) still exists at the shrine, serving as historical evidence of its construction.<ref name="choushi">額田町史、pp.188-189</ref> This plaque predates others such as the one from {{ill|1122|ja|1122nd year|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Hōan|ja|保安|qq=draft}} 3) at {{ill|Chūson-ji|ja|中尊寺|qq=draft}}.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E6%A3%9F%E6%9C%AD-140683 |title=棟札とは |publisher=コトバンク |accessdate=2013-01-21}}</ref> However, the exact date is debated due to questions about its authenticity.<ref name="choushi"/> The plaque was exhibited at the {{ill|Nagoya Pan-Pacific Peace Exposition|ja|名古屋汎太平洋平和博覧会|qq=draft}} in {{ill|1937|ja|1937th year|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Shōwa|ja|昭和|qq=draft}} 12).<ref name="choushi"/>

In {{ill|1894|ja|1894th year|qq=draft}} (Meiji 27), the current main hall, built in {{ill|Nagare-zukuri|ja|流造|qq=draft}} style, was constructed. The Kaguraden was added in {{ill|1935|ja|1935th year|qq=draft}} (Shōwa 10).<ref name="rekishiteki-219-232"/>

A ceremony celebrating the completion of a new worship hall was held on {{ill|October 20|ja|10月20日|qq=draft}}, {{ill|2012|ja|2012nd year|qq=draft}} (Heisei 24).

